After updating my EditorToolbox version from 0.12.12 to 0.14, it looks like the ToolboxEditorToolbar.OnToolbarGui event no longer seems to fire. I've been using it to add extra buttons to the toolbar, like so 

```[UnityEditor.InitializeOnLoad]
    public static class DebugUnityEditorToolbar
    {
        public static bool PreferVRMode {get; private set;}

        static DebugUnityEditorToolbar()
        {
            ToolboxEditorToolbar.OnToolbarGui += OnToolbarGui;
        }

        private static void OnToolbarGui()
        {
            Debug.Log("Hitting OnToolbarGUI");
            GUILayout.FlexibleSpace();

            bool originalGUIState = GUI.enabled;
            GUI.enabled = true;

            // Create the toggle button
            if (GUILayout.Toggle(PreferVRMode, "VRMode?", "Button"))
            {
                if (!PreferVRMode)
                    PreferVRMode = true;
            }
            else
            {
                if (PreferVRMode)
                    PreferVRMode = false;
            }

            // Restore the original GUI enabled state
            GUI.enabled = originalGUIState;
        }
    }
```

This used to work fine, but now it looks like OnToolbarGui isn't being called - this was a really nice feature, would be awesome if there's a way to keep it working 

